Snowballs
Buttery nut cookies rolled in powdered sugar
classic
Sweet, Soft, Nutty

INGREDIENTS:
1 cup unsalted butter, softened
1/2 cup powdered sugar
1 tsp vanilla
2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour
1/4 tsp salt
3/4 cup finely chopped nuts (pecans, walnuts, or almonds)
Powdered sugar for rolling

INSTRUCTIONS:
Preheat oven to 350Â°F
Cream butter and powdered sugar until light and fluffy
Add vanilla and mix well
Gradually add flour and salt, mixing until combined
Stir in chopped nuts
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets
Bake 10-12 minutes until set but not brown
Roll in powdered sugar while warm, then again when cool